programs. Tailoring the Welsh Baccalaureate curriculum to meet industry requirements, creating resources and materials explaining its benefits, and encouraging industry leaders to advocate for the program can also contribute significantly to enhancing employers' understanding and appreciation of the program.&#10;&#10;3. Dafydd Evans acknowledges that there have been negative experiences with the Welsh Baccalaureate, particularly among level 1 and 2 learners who may already be struggling with English and maths resits. He suggests that a more focused curriculum without the additional burden of the Welsh Baccalaureate might better serve these students at lower levels, while reserving its benefits for those at Level 3 with stronger academic foundations.">
