sh Baccalaureate and its benefits, along with the pressure it puts on learners in terms of bureaucracy and workload, has raised questions about whether it truly develops the skills that employers require.&#10;5. Employers prioritize the main qualifications relevant to their industry, such as engineering qualifications for engineers. While they want well-rounded employees, they might not fully understand or value the Welsh Baccalaureate as a means of achieving this goal.">
