etitive programs or applying to prestigious institutions.&#10;&#10;For A-level students and Seren network students, this inconsistent adoption may result in an undervaluation of their Welsh Baccalaureate qualification by certain admissions tutors. Since some universities might not view the Welsh Baccalaureate as equally important as four A-levels or specific subject combinations, these students could face challenges when applying to competitive programs or prestigious institutions. It is essential for students and educators to understand these inconsistencies to make informed decisions about the value of pursuing the Welsh Baccalaureate alongside A-levels or other qualifications.">
