lity in implementation and outcomes, and employer buy-in and recognition. Enhancing communication between educators and employers, promoting a clearer understanding of the Welsh Baccalaureate's goals and benefits, and emphasizing its alignment with industry requirements can contribute to more positive perceptions among employers, ultimately enhancing the program's value in preparing students for employment.">
